<MELItem itemNbr="79-31-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-79-31-01.1.2-79-31-01_FAA">
<Title>Engine Oil Quantity Indicating Systems</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="A" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Before each departure, verify the associated engine oil tank is filled to the recommended capacity.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Oil consumption is within limits.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Repairs are made within three flight days.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Review engine records to verify that oil consumption is within limits and before each departure, verify that oil level is filled to the recommended level (AMM DDG 79-31-01).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Review engine records to verify that oil consumption is within engine manufacturer’s limits or Vietnam Airlines approved limits (if more restrictive).</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Before each departure, verify the associated engine oil tank is filled to the recommended capacity.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>